  "local_port": 38744,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I do not have a surname on passport or any of my education certificates. What should be the most appropriate step now to fix the issue?",
  "response": "If your passport and education certificates do not include a surname and you need to have one added or ensure consistency across your documents, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Gather Supporting Documents:**\n   - **Birth Certificate:** This typically includes your full legal name and can serve as primary evidence.\n   - **National Identification:** If available, documents like a national ID card may also display your full name.\n   - **Legal Name Change Documents (if applicable):** If you've previously changed your name, provide official documentation of that change.\n\n2. **Contact the Passport Issuing Authority:**\n   - **Visit the Official Website or Office:** Look up the passport authority in your country (e.g., Passport Services in the U.S., HM Passport Office in the U.K.).\n   - **Understand the Requirements:** Each country has specific forms and requirements for updating passport information.\n   - **Submit an Application:** Complete the necessary application forms to amend your passport to include your surname. This will likely involve providing your current passport, supporting documents, and possibly paying a fee.\n   - **Provide Proof of Surname:** Ensure you include documents that clearly establish your surname.\n\n3. **Update Education Certificates:**\n   - **Contact Educational Institutions:** Reach out to the registrar's office or the department responsible for issuing certificates at each of your educational institutions.\n   - **Request an Amendment:** Inquire about the process for correcting or updating your certificates to include your surname.\n   - **Submit Necessary Documentation:** Provide your current certificates along with supporting documents (like your birth certificate or updated passport) to validate the change.\n   - **Follow Through:** There may be fees or specific forms to fill out, so ensure you complete all required steps as instructed by the institution.\n\n4. **Ensure Consistency Across All Documents:**\n   - Once your passport and education certificates are updated, verify that all other legal documents (e.g., driver's license, bank accounts, social security records) reflect your full name consistently.\n\n5. **Seek Legal Assistance if Needed:**\n   - If you encounter difficulties or if the process is complex in your jurisdiction, consider consulting with a legal professional who specializes in name changes or administrative law to guide you through the process.\n\n6. **Keep Copies and Documentation:**\n   - After making changes, keep copies of all amended documents and correspondence with authorities for your records and future reference.\n\nBy systematically addressing each document and ensuring you have the necessary legal proof of your surname, you can update your passport and education certificates to include your surname, thereby resolving identification and documentation issues.",
